-- Banco di Sicilia Won’t Buy UniCredit Shares, Repubblica Says
-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 2012-01-08T15:01:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-08/banco-di-sicilia-won-t-buy-unicredit-shares-repubblica-says.html
Banco di Sicilia foundation won’t
take part in  UniCredit SpA (UCG) ’s planned share sale,  la Repubblica 
reported, citing Chairman Giovanni Puglisi.  Puglisi said it’s “inevitable” that new investors will
buy shares during the lender’s capital increase, Repubblica
said. The Banco di Sicilia foundation owns less than 1 percent
in UniCredit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Remondini in Milan at 
 cremondini@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  